sec.p:
mRNA sequencing of transcriptomes of Creso and Svevo durum wheat cultivars revealed four main responses that are all well connected each other:
Slight activation of several transcription factors mainly belonging to bHLH and WRKY families;
Strong up-regulation of three NAS genes that probably sustain the production of the phytosiderophore NA;
Strong up-regulation of the methionine salvage pathway that is tightly connected with NA synthesis and supply the SAM necessary for NA biosynthesis;
Overall up-regulation of different heavy metal transporters; in particular, the NA vacuolar transporters ZIF1, ZIF-like genes, and YSL2 were vigorously activated.
